SIMPLE: opossum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Opossum
<hw>O*pos"sum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of N. American
Indian origin.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any American marsupial of
the genera <gen>Didelphys</gen> and <gen>Chironectes</gen>; called also
<altname>possum</altname>. The common species of the United States is
<spn>Didelphys Virginiana</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Several related species are found in South America. The
water opossum of Brazil (<spn>Chironectes variegatus</spn>), which has
the hind feet, webbed, is provided with a marsupial pouch and with cheek
pouches. It is called also <altname>yapock</altname>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Opossum mouse</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Flying mouse</cref>, under <er>Flying</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Opossum shrimp</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any schizopod
crustacean of the genus <gen>Mysis</gen> and allied genera. See
<er>Schizopoda</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oppidan</ent>⟦br⟧
